LEGAL NOTICE
By Registered Post Acknowledgement Due & By Email

Date: {TODAY_DATE}

To:
The Managing Director,
{BANK_NAME}, FASTag Issuing Bank,
Corporate Office, __________

Subject: Statutory notice under Section 80 of the Code of Civil Procedure 1908 + RBI Master Direction DBR.No.Leg.BC.27/09.07.005/2017-20 + IHMCL FASTag SOP 2024 — multiple FASTag deductions at plaza {PLAZA_NAME} total Rs. {AMOUNT} (UTRs {TXN_ID} / {TXN_ID_2} etc.) on vehicle {VEHICLE_NO} (Tag {TAG_ID}) on {TXN_DATETIME}

Sir / Madam,

1. Under instructions from and on behalf of my client, {USER_NAME}, holder of FASTag {TAG_ID} on vehicle {VEHICLE_NO}, I hereby serve this Legal Notice under Section 80, CPC read with RBI Master Direction DBR.No.Leg.BC.27/09.07.005/2017-20 and IHMCL FASTag SOP 2024 on the matters set out below.

2. The facts are:
   (i) On {TXN_DATETIME}, the FASTag Tag deducted my client's Tag-balance {NUM_TXNS} times at plaza {PLAZA_NAME} for an aggregate of Rs. {AMOUNT};
   (ii) The acquirer (the Concessionaire / MEP / IRB at plaza {PLAZA_NAME}) is bound to reconcile the deduction with the ANPR / lane-camera record of *physical crossing*, per IHMCL SOP § 6.1;
   (iii) No reconciliation was provided despite my client's letters dated {COMPLAINT_DATE} (ref {TICKET_NO}), {LAST_FOLLOWUP_DATE} (ref 2), and the latest on {DATE_FINAL_LETTER};
   (iv) The Issuer Bank ({BANK_NAME}) has declined liability on the ground that the dispute 'is between the acquirer and the customer', which is contrary to Section 6.2 of the IHMCL SOP that allocates *both* issuer and acquirer responsibility on the customer — the issuer has a duty to cooperate.

3. Hence this Notice. The addressee is called upon to:
   (a) Jointly and severally refund Rs. {AMOUNT} to the underlying VPA, within fifteen (15) days of receipt;
   (b) Pay compensation of Rs. {COMPENSATION_DUE} per RBI Master Circular DBR.No.Leg.BC.27/09.07.005/2017-18;
   (c) Pay Rs. {OUT_OF_POCKET} for the advocate fee, postal and stationery charges;
   (d) Issue a public statement to the issuer's other Tag-holders informing them of the migration path to the correct acquirer and of the freeze period during the pendency of these disputes.

4. Default on the above shall entitle my client to file:
   (a) Section 35-A direction to RBI;
   (b) IHMCL appellate under IHMCL SOP § 13;
   (c) Complaint before the appropriate Consumer Commission under Section 35 of the Consumer Protection Act, 2019;
   (d) Section 200 CrPC complaint (now Bhartiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita 223) for unreasonable denial of lawful claim.

5. A copy of this Notice is retained in my office for filing before any Court / Commission / Forum.

Yours truly,

{ADVOCATE_NAME}
Pleader / Advocate, {PIO_OFFICE}
Enrolment: [Bar Council Regn. No. _______]

For and on behalf of:
{USER_NAME}, {ADDRESS}, Mobile {MOBILE_NO}, Email {EMAIL}

